<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1693,2044]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,487,1693,1720]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Description (Fig. 34 and 35).</emphasis>
Fronto-orbital setae in four pairs, two upper setae reclinate and two lower setae inclinate; orbital setulae proclinate; arista enlarged basally; gena narrow, 1/10 as high as eye; dorsocentrals 0+3 (anterior only a little longer than acrostichal setulae); acrostichal setulae in 4 rows; wing length 
<quantity box="[1130,1219,1766,1793]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
; costa extending to R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[170,196,1820,1834]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">4+5</subScript>
; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[227,252,1820,1834]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[327,353,1820,1834]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">4+5</subScript>
parallel
<subScript attach="left" box="[441,445,1820,1834]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">,</subScript>
ending near the anterior portion of the wing; costal section between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1243,1268,1820,1834]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1344,1370,1820,1834]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">4+5</subScript>
about half length of costal section between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[587,595,1856,1870]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">1</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[662,687,1856,1870]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">2+3</subScript>
; vein dm-cu absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1693,2044]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1873,1900]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Coloration.</emphasis>
Fronto-orbital plate greyish-brown; frons brown; gena brownish-yellow; face and lunule with a faint greyish pruinosity; antenna brown; arista light-brown; palpus brown; body predominantly brown, with the notopleuron, dorsal and posterior border of the anepisternum, dorsal and anterior border of the anepimeron yellowish; mesonotum with pruinosity grey; legs light-brown, with apex of femur and base of tibia yellow; base of wing yellow; halter yellow; calypter yellowish, fringe white; abdomen centrally brown with margin yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3259218/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" startId="26.[151,234,1967,1992]" targetBox="[203,1425,195,1941]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1967,2028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,425,1967,1992]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">PLATE 9. Figures 34–37.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Monteiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Esposito, 2019" authorityName="Monteiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Esposito" authorityYear="2019" box="[431,670,1968,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Phytomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varronivora" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[431,670,1968,1992]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
Phytomyza 
<taxonomicName box="[549,670,1969,1992]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" rank="species" species="varronivora" status="sp. nov.">varronivora</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[678,798,1967,1992]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[678,759,1968,1992]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
34.
</emphasis>
Adult, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1039,1967,1992]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">35.</emphasis>
Adult, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1245,1277,1967,1992]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">36.</emphasis>
Male genitalia, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,313,2003,2028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">37.</emphasis>
Male genitalia, ventral view. Scale = 0.5 mm in Fig. 34 and 35; Fig. 36 and 37 = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,971]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,579,152,179]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Male genitalia (Fig. 36 and 40).</emphasis>
Epandrium with three projections internally; surstylus fused to epandrium, bearing 13 elongated stout setae; cercus slender; hypandrium V-shaped with 3 or 4 setae basally (Fig. 36 and 37); aedeagus (Fig. 36 and 49): basiphallus sclerotized, forming two slender U-shaped plates; mesophallus short and globose, slightly sclerotized; distiphallus forming two short tubules; ejaculatory apodeme forming an enlarged blade apically (Fig. 40).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,971]" box="[199,1071,332,360]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,441,332,359]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Host-plant (Fig. 41).</emphasis>
Boraginaceae— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cham.) Borhidi." authorityName="Borhidi." baseAuthorityName="Cham." box="[628,1071,333,360]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Varronia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multispicata">
<emphasis box="[628,871,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Varronia multispicata</emphasis>
(Cham.) Borhidi.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
